00042         int minx = MAXU;

00044         int maxx = centerb.getNumLat() - minx;
00045         int maxy = centerb.getNumLon() - miny;
00046         for (int i=0; i < data1.getNumLat(); ++i){

00048                 if (i < minx || j < miny || i > maxx || j > maxy){

00053         Complex[][] in2 = FFT2D.fft(FFT2D.zeropad(centerb));

00055         // find phase shift at this point
00056         for (int i=0; i < in1.length; ++i) for (int j=0; j < in1[0].length; ++j){
00057             in1[i][j] = in1[i][j].multiply(in2[i][j].conjugate());
00058             in1[i][j] = in1[i][j].multiply( 1.0 / in1[i][j].norm() );
00059         }
00060         // take ifft
00061         Complex[][] result = FFT2D.ifft(in1);
00062         
00063         // find location at which the cross-power specturm is maximum
00064         double bestValue = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
00065         int startx = 0; // result.length/2 - MAXU;
00066         int starty = 0; // result[0].length/2 - MAXV;
00067         int endx = result.length; // /2 + MAXU;
00068         int endy = result[0].length; // /2 + MAXV;
00069         for (int i=startx; i < endx; ++i) for (int j=starty; j < endy; ++j){
00070             if ( result[i][j].normsq() > bestValue ){
00071                 bestValue = result[i][j].real;
00072                 motNS = -i;
00073                 motEW = -j;
00074             }
00075         }
00076         
00077         // we don't want a 345-degree phase shift; we want it to be 15-degrees
00078         if ( Math.abs(motNS) > result.length/2 ){
00079             if (motNS < 0) motNS += result.length;
00080             else motNS -= result.length;
00081         }
00082         if ( Math.abs(motEW) > result[0].length/2 ){
00083             if (motEW < 0) motEW += result[0].length;
00084             else motEW -= result[0].length;

00091         double sumx = 0;
00092         double sumy = 0;
00093         double sumwt = 0;
00094         int N = 0;
00095         for (int i=0; i < a.getNumLat(); ++i) for (int j=0; j < a.getNumLon(); ++j){
00096             double wt = a.getValue(i,j);
00097             sumx += i * wt;
00098             sumy += j * wt;
00099             sumwt += wt;
00100             ++N;

00102         return new Pixel((int)Math.round(sumx/sumwt), (int)Math.round(sumy/sumwt), (int)Math.round(sumwt/N));
